  "slug": "slow-cooked-pork-chop-with-mushroom-gravy",
  "name": "Slow Cook Pork Chop with Mushroom Gravy",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "One of the easiest and best tasting pork chop recipes that I tried is Slow Cook Pork Chop with Mushroom Gravy. Get to know why.",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Combine pork chops, mushrooms, water, beef cube, salt, and pepper in a slow cooker."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Slow cook on high setting for 3 to 4 hours."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Remove the pork chops and arrange in individual plates. Leave the sauce in the slow cooker."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Meanwhile, pour-in the water with cornstarch on the remaining sauce. Stir. Note: add water if needed."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Pour-in the mushroom gravy (sauce) over the pork chops."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Serve with brown rice. Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 4,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 180,
  "preparation_time_minutes": 5,
